# Cursor Rules for ask-t Personal Knowledge Hub

## Language & Communication
- Always respond in Japanese (日本語で応答)
- Use clear, concise explanations
- Provide code comments in English for consistency

## Project Context
This is a personal knowledge hub built with Docusaurus that includes:
- Daily TODO management via GitHub Issues
- Public/private notes (Notion alternative)
- Project portfolio and documentation

## Coding Standards

### TypeScript/React
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use proper type annotations (avoid `any`)
- Follow React best practices

### File Organization
- Components in `src/components/`
- Pages in `src/pages/`
- Data files in `src/data/`
- Notes in `docs/notes/`
- Project docs in `docs/projects/`

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS classes
- Custom CSS in `src/css/custom.css`
- Use CSS variables for theming (--fg, --muted, --card-bg, etc.)

## GitHub Issue Management
When working with GitHub Issues for daily TODOs:
- Use `gh` CLI for issue operations
- Label daily TODOs with `daily-todo`
- Format: `YYYY-MM-DD Daily TODO` for issue titles

```bash
# Issue操作
gh issue list --label daily-todo
gh issue view <number>
gh issue edit <number> --body "..."
gh issue create --title "YYYY-MM-DD Daily TODO" --label daily-todo
```

## Common Commands
```bash
# Development
npm run dev          # Start dev server
npm run build        # Build for production
npm run serve        # Preview build locally
```

## Notes Management
ノートは `docs/notes/` に配置:

- `docs/notes/tech/` - 技術メモ
- `docs/notes/learning/` - 学習記録
- `docs/notes/ideas/` - アイデア

### ノートのFrontmatter
```markdown
---
title: ノートタイトル
tags: [tag1, tag2]
